    <text id="B0276T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Bond informs Jordan that a claim has been rejected. Although the case was
                    resolved while Jordan was the Agent in Staunton, it appears to be related to his
                    previous post.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Law and Claim Office<lb/>S. R. BOND,<lb/>Will practice in the Courts of the
                    District, the Court of Claims, and before all the Departments.<lb/>488 1/2
                    Seventh Street,
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Colonel">Col.</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="John">Jno</abbr> W. Jordan<lb/>Farmville, <abbr
                            expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1868-06-11">June 11, 1868.</date>
                        <name type="place">Washington D.C.,</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute><abbr expan="Dear">Dr.</abbr> Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>Enclosed please find discharge of Randall Brown whose claim has been rejected on
                    the ground that he has <abbr expan="received">rec<hi rend="super">d</hi></abbr>
                    $100, the 1st installment - all he is entitled to.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very <abbr expan="Respectfully">Respy</abbr> Yours</salute>
                    <signed>S.R. Bond</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
